The paper discusses the challenges of testing and analyzing programs containing floating-point computations, which is a common problem in software engineering (cs.SE). It also addresses the issue of defining the semantics of floating-point implementations, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper mentions the role of compilers in affecting the semantics of floating-point computations, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR). Finally, the paper proposes solutions for implementing analysis software, which is related to formal methods (cs.FL).
